I think the `try`/`except` here can be safely omitted:
1) I don't think this library has ever worked without django.contrib.staticfiles;
2) as I understand it, the `django.templatetags.static` / `{% load static %}` version of the tag is *only* useful for non-staticfiles-enabled projects (which we can ignore due to point 1); for everyone else, the `django.contrib.staticfiles` / `{% load staticfiles %}` version of the tag is better in all respects;
3) even if staticfiles was omitted from INSTALLED_APPS the import would presumably still succeed.

Would you agree, or is there something I'm missing?

